-- Bank Negara Indonesia, Sarana Menara: Indonesia Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2011-12-28T01:51:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/bank-negara-indonesia-sarana-menara-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual (JCI)  moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The Jakarta Composite index fell 0.2 percent to 3,789.43.  Energy companies: Crude-oil futures rose 1.7 percent to
$101.34 a barrel in New York yesterday, gaining for a sixth
straight day in the longest rally since the period ended Nov. 8,
2010.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC)  , Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 1 percent to 2,450 rupiah and
 PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  , the second largest, advanced
1.2 percent to 175 rupiah.  PT Sarana Menara Nusantara (TOWR)  : A unit of the company
obtained a 2 trillion rupiah ($218 million) loan from  PT Bank
Negara Indonesia (BBNI)  , Sarana Menara said in a statement to
the Indonesia Stock Exchange. PT Profesional Telekomunikasi
Indonesia will use the proceeds to acquire telecommunication
towers and buy stakes in tower companies, the company said.
Sarana Menara was unchanged at 10,000 rupiah when it last traded
Dec. 23. Bank Negara Indonesia, the nation’s third-biggest state
owned bank, fell 1.9 percent to 3,850 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
